data: In separate questions, respondents were asked if there is a place that they usually go if they are sick and need health care, and if so (or if more than one place), to indicate the kind of place. Respondents who indicated their place of usual care was a hospital emergency room were not classified as having a usual place of care.
caption: Percentage of having a usual place of health care for adults aged 18 and over (95% confidence intervals), United States
